FT  04 AUG 94 / Pounds 51,000 rise for grid chairman
Mr David Jefferies, chairman of the National Grid power transmission
company, saw his total emoluments rise to Pounds 359,000 in the last
financial year from Pounds 308,000 in 1992-93. His salary rose to Pounds
271,000 from Pounds 236,000 and his performance-related bonus to Pounds
59,000 from Pounds 44,000.
The total includes a relocation allowance of Pounds 25,000 to cover house
moving expenses when the company relocated its headquarters from London to
the Midlands.
